Problem


Today’s shared communication services are fragmented across network devices, digital signs and single-purpose digital kiosks
 


Managing internet access, voice, data and information services in shared spaces remains difficult


Integration of various services that were never designed to work together is an increasing challenge


Not unlike the pre iPhone era, when people needed a phone, a blackberry, a PalmPilot, a camera, a GPS etc.




Cost and complexity are out of control






Solution


LQD provides Palo, the “iPad of the Streets”
 


A sidewalk device that unifies hardware and software to bridge the digital divide in communities around the world












How it Works


Palo better informs, connects, protects, and engages communities


































