Commonly Asked Questions

Why would a traveler choose Tesloop over flights?
Tesloop routes are typically 100-300 miles. For 100-200 mile range, such as Portland to Seattle,  Tesloop costs 60% less than flights and takes 1 hour less!
For 200-300 mile range, such as Vegas to LA,  Tesloop still costs less than flights, takes about 1 more hour but the traveler does not have to wait in line, go through security, be cut off from the Internet and phone. With Tesloop, the client can work, talk on the phone, go online, etc. during the entire ride.

More importantly, the traveler will contribute to reducing carbon emission and pollution with Tesloop while the air travel will add to carbon emission and pollution.







